// Project-local livespec configuration for livespec-driver-codex.
//
// This repo is the reference Codex Driver for the livespec family.
// It dogfoods livespec: the SPECIFICATION/ tree at the repo root is the
// live spec for the Driver's own seam (binding shape, core-root
// resolution, plugin/marketplace manifest, and the Driver-shipped hook
// bundle), and it evolves through /livespec:seed / propose-change /
// revise / doctor / prune-history / critique — exactly the lifecycle
// every consumer project uses.
//
// Scope discipline: this spec governs ONLY what the Driver owns. The
// operation prose, the reference spec-side CLIs, the JSON schemas, and
// the built-in templates all live in livespec core; this tree defers to
// core by citation and never restates the upstream contract. When any
// rule here appears to conflict with livespec core's SPECIFICATION/, the
// upstream rule wins (see SPECIFICATION/README.md §"Upstream pointers").
//
// Authority: livespec/SPECIFICATION/spec.md
//   §"Contract + reference implementations architecture" (the Driver is
//   the thin, agent-runtime-specific binding layer; core is agnostic to
//   it) and livespec/SPECIFICATION/contracts.md §"Plugin distribution",
//   §"Driver-shipped hooks".
//
// DEFERRED — beads tenant: the per-repo beads/Dolt tenant CONNECTION
// block (and the matching committed .beads/config.yaml) is NOT yet
// provisioned for this repo. It is intentionally OMITTED here and will
// be added in a later family-infra phase, mirroring the
// livespec-driver-claude pattern (tenant name == repo name; TCP-only,
// NO socket key; password supplied via BEADS_DOLT_PASSWORD at bd-call
// time and NEVER committed).
{
  "template": "livespec",
  "spec_root": "SPECIFICATION",
  "implementation": { "plugin": "livespec-orchestrator-beads-fabro" },
  "livespec-driver-codex": {
    "compat": {
      // semver range and pinned tag against livespec core. The pin is
      // "master" during bootstrap (always-HEAD dogfooding); doctor's
      // contract-version-compatibility invariant fires `warn` against a
      // "master" pin, which is expected pre-1.0.
      "livespec": ">=0.1.0,<1.0.0",
      "pinned": "v0.2.0"
    }
  }
}
